sement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDocumenting%20changing%20food%20habits%20across%20geographies%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20a%20nondescript%20food%20stall%20in%20Ladakh%20where%20JNU%20(Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20New%20Delhi)%20PhD%20scholar%2C%20Fida%20Husain%E2%80%99s%20aunt%20Ama%20Haji%20would%20get%20her%20fill%20of%20%3Cem%3EYarkhandi%20pulao%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20her%20essay%2C%20Fida%20writes%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3EYarkandi%20polla%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereflects%20the%20cultural%20heritage%20of%20Ladakh%20as%20a%20confluence%20of%20cultures.%20%E2%80%9CMade%20the%20traditional%20way%20%E2%80%94%20slow-cooked%20in%20a%20heavy%20stone%20pot%20called%20a%20%3Cem%3Edoltok%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20%3Cem%3ELadakhi%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20the%20dish%20was%20said%20to%20be%20symbolic%20of%20the%20big%20hearts%20(read%3A%20deep%20pockets)%20of%20the%20hosts%20for%20their%20guests.%20This%20bounty%20was%20proven%20by%20the%20amount%20of%20fat%2Fghee%20dripping%20down%20one%E2%80%99s%20elbows%20while%20eating.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFun%20fact%3A%20Ladakh%20was%20a%20stranger%20to%20rice%2C%20the%20protagonist%20of%20the%20dish%2C%20until%20about%20seven%20decades%20ago.%20It%20was%20improved%20transport%20links%20and%20connectivity%20that%20transformed%20the%20once%20luxury%20item%20into%20a%20staple%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F282445%2Findia-in-pics-ten-local-ladakhi-dish-history-culture-kunzes-angmo-instagram%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Ladakhi%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%203147px)%20100vw%2C%203147px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%223147%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tarana%20Husain%20Khan%20interacted%20with%20a%20number%20of%20culinary%20virtuosos%20to%20understand%20the%20history%20behind%20South%20Asian%20cuisine%20and%20its%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20current%20gastronomic%20landscape%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982.jpg%203147w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-300x288.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-500x480.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-768x737.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-1536x1474.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-2048x1965.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-1200x1151.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FIMG_3367-1730813982-150x144.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-374455%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223019%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETarana%20Husain%20Khan%20interacted%20with%20many%20culinary%20virtuosos%20to%20understand%20the%20history%20behind%20South%20Asian%20cuisine%20and%20its%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20current%20gastronomic%20landscape%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20the%20Northeast%2C%20local%20sensibilities%20dictated%20recipes%2C%20in%20Central%20and%20Eastern%20India%2C%20it%20was%20royal%20customs%20that%20did.%20This%20is%20what%20Tarana%20discovered%20during%20her%20stay%20at%20Bhopal%E2%80%99s%20Jehan%20Numa%20Palace%20Hotel%20%E2%80%94%20which%20belongs%20to%20the%20descendants%20of%20Nawab%20Sultan%20Jahan%20Begum%E2%80%99s%20second%20son%2C%20Nawab%20Muhammad%20Obaidullah%20Khan%2C%20and%20is%20known%20for%20its%20preservation%20of%20heirloom%20recipes%20of%20Bhopal%E2%80%99s%20Nawabi%20cuisine.%20Here%2C%20she%20enjoyed%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20two%20dishes%20with%20a%20rich%20history%3A%20the%20%3Cem%3EBhopali%20rezala%20%3C%2Fem%3E(chicken%20cooked%20with%20spinach)%20%E2%80%94%20which%20she%20learnt%2C%20amalgamates%20the%20local%20flavours%20with%20%3Cem%3EAwadhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Mughal%20cuisine%20and%20is%20popular%20in%20West%20Bengal%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20unique%20mincemeat%20preparation).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharing%20more%20about%20these%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CBhopalis%20apparently%20prepared%20%3Cem%3Erezala%20%3C%2Fem%3Efrom%20peacock%20meat%20until%20hunting%20peacocks%20was%20banned.%20As%20for%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F349748%2Flaal-maas-history-recipe-best-places-to-eat-in-rajasthan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunting%20traditions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Bhopal.%20Upon%20the%20killing%20of%20an%20animal%20%E2%80%93%20usually%20nilgai%2C%20deer%20or%20gazelle%20%E2%80%93%20its%20meat%20was%20coarsely%20chopped%20or%20sliced%20into%20slivers%20while%20still%20warm%2C%20and%20immediately%20fried%20with%20some%20basic%20ingredients%20on%20a%20campfire.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20made%20for%20a%20rustic%20meal%20for%20the%20hunters.%20The%20modern%20version%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Efilfora%20%3C%2Fem%3Eincludes%20hand-chopped%20mincemeat%20cooked%20